Rules:
- Map each raw header to the SINGLE best-matching canonical field, or omit if no good match.
- Confidence: 1.0 = exact match, 0.9 = clear synonym, 0.7 = probable match, < 0.6 = uncertain.
- overall_confidence: average of all per-column confidence scores.
- entity_type: the CAFM entity type that best describes this spreadsheet's content.
- unmatched: headers with no clear canonical match (keep them — never drop data).
